In Michoacan, they analyze the possibility of compiling "glass by voice"
According to the data published by PREP, the difference between the first and second elections of the governor is less than 27 per cent. No votes of 879 of 6074 elections have yet been calculated.
The possibility of compiling "vote by voice" appeared in this year's elections in Michoacan, where, in accordance with the statements published by the Preliminary Election Programme (PREP), the difference between the first and the second seat in the Governor's elections of at least 27 per cent has not yet been recorded by the votes 879 of the total 6074 electoral counties.
In this regard, the President of the General Council of the Electoral Institute in Michoacan (IEM), María de los Ángeles Llanderal Zaragoza, recalled that several days ago, on 9 November, the Election Authority approved a number of measures to harmonise local standards with the Federal Electoral Reform.
As it will be recalled, Michoacan has not officially confirmed his political constitution or its National Electoral Code or the Electoral Justice Act. The State Congress has approved reforms shortly before the legal period for their entry into force in this election period, and Governor Leonel Godoy Rangel recalled their publication in a specified period in the Official State Journal that he had any objections against them.
On 9 November, the Supreme State Court (SCJN) resolved the constitutional dispute initiated by local legislative power and declared the vote of the head of the State in the constitutional reforms as "incorrect and illegal" because he has no right to "allow or vet".
On the question of the possibility of compiling "glass by voice" María de los Ángeles Llanderal replied that by approval of the relevant measures, the General Council of IEM will be able to perform partial and general electoral computation by the local electoral authority.
In this way, a partial summary of votes, one or more electoral packages, will be possible under the following conditions: the election results do not agree; there is no record of the computation of votes and the calculation in the corresponding field or is not available by the Chairperson; or if there are errors and apparent violations of the electoral results.
Furthermore, the total recalculation of votes in all election urnas will be possible if there is an indication that the difference between the potential winner of elections and the candidate in the second place is smaller or equal to one percentage point; when an explicit application of the representative and/or the coalition that proposed the candidate in the second place appears at the beginning of the session.
The total recalculation of votes will also be possible when the difference between the probably winner and the candidate in the second place is equal or less than one percentage point and when there is an explicit request of the political party whose candidate ended in the second place. In such a case, the electoral packages with partial computation will be deleted.
It should be mentioned that in such a situation there are elections in Morelia, where, according to PREP, the difference between the first and second place of less than 0,16%, even though 129 of the total 923 elections have not yet been compiled.
